# Lab Notes — Enterprise Lab (pfSense + Windows Server)

## 1. Environment Summary
- Hyper-V-based lab
- pfSense as router/firewall
- Windows Server 2019/2022 for AD DS, DNS, and DHCP
- Segmented subnets: 192.168.1.0/24 and 192.168.2.0/24

## 2. Key Observations
- DHCP failover (Load Balance 50/50) works consistently
- DNS forwarders to Cloudflare improve external resolution speed
- Cross-subnet routing is stable via pfSense

## 3. Troubleshooting Notes
- If clients don’t get a DHCP lease → check firewall rules
- If DNS fails → verify forwarders on SRV-DC01
- If pfSense WAN unreachable → check main router DHCP/static mapping

